Mini Drone for Cattle Farming
Overview
The Mini Drone for Cattle Farming project aims to leverage drone technology to assist farmers in monitoring and managing their cattle more efficiently. By providing real-time aerial surveillance and data collection, the drone helps in improving the health and safety of livestock, enhancing farm operations, and enabling data-driven decision making.

Features
Real-time Monitoring: Observe cattle movement and behavior from an aerial perspective.
Automated Health Checks: Use integrated sensors to monitor the health and wellness of cattle.
GPS Tracking: Locate lost or stray cattle with GPS-enabled tracking.
Data Analysis: Analyze collected data to improve pasture management and resource allocation.
Technologies Used
Drone Hardware: Mini drone equipped with necessary sensors and cameras.
GPS and Sensors: For tracking and health monitoring.
Machine Learning: Analyze cattle behavior and health data.
IoT: Real-time data transmission and monitoring.
Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/minidrone-cattle-farming.git
cd minidrone-cattle-farming
Setup Drone Hardware:

Follow the instructions provided in the hardware_setup.md file for setting up the drone hardware.
Install Software Dependencies:

bash
Copy code
# For backend
pip install -r requirements.txt

# For frontend
npm install
Configure GPS and Sensors:

Refer to gps_sensor_setup.md for configuration details.
Usage
Launch the Backend Server:

bash
Copy code
python server.py
Start the Frontend Application:

bash
Copy code
npm start
Connect to the Drone:

Ensure your drone is powered on and connected to the network.
Begin Monitoring:

Access the web application and start monitoring your cattle in real-time.
